Karma + Jasmine + RequireJS:
============================

http://karma-runner.github.io/0.12/intro/installation.html
http://monicalent.com/blog/2015/02/11/karma-tests-angular-js-require-j/
http://karma-runner.github.io/0.8/plus/RequireJS.html
https://github.com/kjbekkelund/karma-requirejs

# Install Karma + components:
-----------------------------

# This will install karma, karma-jasmine and karma-chrome-launcher packages into node_modules in
# your current working directory and also save these as devDependencies in package.json, so that
# any other developer working on the project will only have to do npm install in order to get all
# these dependencies installed.
# npm install karma karma-jasmine karma-phantomjs-launcher karma-requirejs --save-dev
sudo npm install karma karma-jasmine karma-chrome-launcher karma-requirejs --save-dev

# Install karma-cli globally.
sudo npm install -g karma-cli

sudo npm install karma-htmlfile-reporter --save-dev
sudo npm install karma-coverage --save-dev
sudo npm install --save-dev angular-mocks
sudo npm install --save-dev karma-mocha karma-chai
sudo npm install karma-sinon --save-dev
sudo npm install karma-jasmine-jquery --save-dev
sudo npm install karma-jasmine-async --save-dev
sudo npm install karma-ng-html2js-preprocessor --save-dev

--

You can install ngMock using npm, bower, or manually. I'll be using npm to install our dependencies:

$ npm install --save angular
$ npm install --save-dev angular-mocks
